TASK_DESCRIPTION=Add a fun animated 'Thinking...' spinner to the doey intent fallback / conversational CLI while waiting for Haiku response. Reference implementation: /home/doey/GitHub/claude-harness — find the 'Thinking...' animation code and replicate the animation style. Instead of 'Thinking...', cycle through these custom words: Doeying, Snootling, Waggening, Snorfeling, Cozymaxxing, Ruffling, Floofing, Scampering, Sniffvestigating, Recombobulating. Each word should animate with dots (e.g. 'Snootling...' with animated dots) and cycle to the next word. This is for the shell-based intent fallback wait state — show while waiting for the Haiku API response. Must be bash 3.2 compatible.
